(d)  if he becomes bankrupt;
(e)  if he is of unsound mind or otherwise incapable of
discharging his duties;
(f)
if he fails to comply with his obligations under section
92;
(g)  if his performance as a member of the Appeal Tribunal
has been unsatisfactory for a significant period of time;
(h)  if his appointment is revoked by the Minister; or
(i)
if his resignation is accepted by the Minister.
